jobs.prompt:
Read `03_outreach_angles.json`. For each record, call the `praxis_integration` MCP tool over the workflow MCP bridge (HTTP to `http://host.docker.internal:8420/mcp`) with action `create_note`. You run in a Docker worker that has NO `praxis` CLI — do NOT shell out to `praxis`. Use the SAME MCP bridge wrapper as `pull_crm_snapshot`: write `_push_driver.py` that imports `runtime.workflow.mcp_session.mint_workflow_mcp_session_token` from `/workspace/Code&DBs/Workflow`, mints a token from `PRAXIS_EXECUTION_BUNDLE`, and POSTs JSON-RPC `tools/call` to the bridge.

Per-record payload:

```json
{
  "action": "call",
  "integration_id": "hubspot",
  "integration_action": "create_note",
  "args": {
    "properties": {"hs_note_body": "<angle_markdown>", "hs_timestamp": "<epoch_ms_now>"},
    "associations": [
      {"to":{"id":"<deal_id>"},"types":[{"associationCategory":"HUBSPOT_DEFINED","associationTypeId":214}]},
      {"to":{"id":"<contact_id>"},"types":[{"associationCategory":"HUBSPOT_DEFINED","associationTypeId":202}]}
    ]
  }
}
```

The MCP response envelope is `{status:'succeeded', data:{response:{id:'<note_id>', ...}}}`. Capture `data.response.id` as `note_id`. Write pairs to `artifacts/hubspot_enrichment_20260418/04_note_ids.json` as `[{deal_id, contact_id, note_id, hubspot_status}]`. On failure, record `{hubspot_status:'failed', error_detail:<truncated>}` — do NOT abort the whole run for a single failed note.
